                        "commitMessage": "feat(entries): rework auto-expire — 1-month JST cutoff, 未応募 marker, two-step guard, chunked updates (T-067 phase B)\n\n- Cutoff: 2 weeks → JST calendar month (toLocaleDateString + Date.UTC\n  with month overflow). Avoids UTC-based date drift on Railway.\n- Marker: only entryFlagDetail=\"未応募\" + isActive=false. Drops the\n  previous 辞退 family writes (companyFlag/personFlag) — withdrawal\n  is the wrong record when the candidate never applied.\n- Two-step guard: live UPDATE only when dry_run=false AND confirm=true.\n  Missing either yields a calc-only response, so an accidental hit\n  cannot mutate the DB.\n- Chunked updates: 50 IDs per updateMany with per-chunk timing logged.\n  Spreads load across the request instead of one massive transaction.\n- Dedup recalculateSubStatusIfAuto by candidateId — same-candidate\n  rows in the same batch trigger one recompute, not N.\n- Response now includes cutoff, oldest/newest target entryDate,\n  chunk_log and total_duration_ms for the staging validation step.\n\nSeparated from the migration restoration commit (T-067 phase A) so\nthe deploy footprint per push stays minimal.",
